sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Engineer / Spark-Submit
    participant CM as Cluster Manager
    participant Driver as Spark Driver (SparkSession)
    participant Exec as Executor Worker Nodes
    participant HDFS as Shared Storage (HDFS/S3)

    User->>CM: Submit Spark Application (spark-submit)
    CM->>CM: Allocate Resource for Driver
    CM->>Driver: Start Driver Process (JVM)
    Driver->>Driver: Initialize SparkContext / DAGScheduler / TaskScheduler
    Driver->>CM: Register App & Request Executor Resources
    CM->>Exec: Launch Executor JVM Processes
    Exec->>Driver: Register Executors and Report CPU Cores/RAM
    
    Note over Driver: User Code Execution Begins (Actions triggered)
    Driver->>Driver: Build Logical Plan (RDD lineage)
    Driver->>Driver: DAGScheduler splits RDD plan into Stages
    Driver->>Driver: TaskScheduler submits Tasks per Stage (TaskSet)
    
    Driver->>Exec: Dispatch Tasks (Serialized bytecode)
    activate Exec
    Exec->>HDFS: Read input split data blocks
    Note over Exec: Execute pipeline in memory (Transformations)
    Exec->>Driver: Send TaskCompletion / Status Updates
    deactivate Exec
    
    Driver->>Driver: Collect results / Write final output
    Driver->>CM: Unregister Application
    Driver->>Driver: Stop SparkSession and terminate JVM
    CM->>Exec: Terminate Executors (Reclaim resources)
